.TH NOTEPAD++ 1 "2026-02" "Notepad++ 8.7.5" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
notepad++ \- powerful GTK3 text editor
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B notepad++
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIFILE\fR...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B notepad++
is a feature\-rich text editor built on GTK3 and the Scintilla editing
component. It provides syntax highlighting for 30+ programming languages,
tabbed editing, find\-in\-files, macro recording, a plugin system, and more.
.PP
This is the Linux/GTK3 port of the original Windows Notepad++ application.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n " LINE"
Open the first file at line number \fILINE\fR (1\-based).
.TP
.BI \-c " COL"
Position the caret at column \fICOL\fR after jumping to the target line.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Print a brief help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/notepad++/settings.conf
Persistent application settings (window geometry, theme, tab width, \&...).
.TP
.I ~/.config/notepad++/session.conf
List of open files saved on exit (used when \fIrestore session\fR is enabled).
.TP
.I ~/.config/notepad++/macros.conf
Named macros recorded in the editor.
.TP
.I <exe\-dir>/plugins/*.so
Plugin shared libraries loaded at startup.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TS
l l.
Ctrl+N	New file
Ctrl+O	Open file
Ctrl+S	Save file
Ctrl+Shift+S	Save As
Ctrl+W	Close tab
Ctrl+Z / Ctrl+Y	Undo / Redo
Ctrl+F	Find
Ctrl+H	Find & Replace
Ctrl+Shift+F	Find in Files
F3 / Shift+F3	Find Next / Previous
Ctrl+G	Go to Line
Ctrl+D	Duplicate line
Ctrl+Shift+L	Delete line
Ctrl+/	Toggle comment
Ctrl+F2	Toggle bookmark
F2 / Shift+F2	Next / Previous bookmark
Ctrl+Shift+R	Record macro
Ctrl+Shift+P	Play back macro
Ctrl+F5	Run external program
Ctrl++/\-/0	Zoom in / out / reset
.TE
.SH EXAMPLES
Open a file and jump to line 42:
.PP
.nf
    notepad++ -n 42 /path/to/source.cpp
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gedit (1),
.BR kate (1),
.BR vim (1)
